If you need a custom component with a focus method, I think you need to use a class component, and [refs](https://reactjs.org/docs/refs-and-the-dom.html):

```javascript
class Input extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props);
    this.inputRef = React.createRef();
  }

  focus() {
    this.inputRef.current.focus();
  }

  render() {
    return &lt;input {...this.props} ref={this.inputRef}/&gt;
  }
}
```

