    })
for more https://firebase.google.com/docs/firestore/manage-data/add-data

From what I understand, your use case is to have a &quot;ToDo list&quot; collection, to save several ToDo&#39;s. Each ToDo (in theory) should have an id, a name and a list of task.

I can see from your Todo model that you are missing the list of &quot;tasks&quot; inside the ToDo. In order to have a ToDo list with tasks you should add an array of &quot;tasks&quot; objects inside your ToDo. And update the array accordingly to the end user&#39;s interactions. 

For example, you want to add/update/delete tasks to an already existing ToDo list, you can do so by using the method &quot;[set][1]&quot; that @yash-gandhi mentioned on their answer.

With something like:

    db.collection(&quot;todos&quot;).doc(&quot;todo1&quot;).set({
    id: &quot;todo1&quot;,
    name: &quot;My first Todo&quot;,
    tasks: [
      {
       desc: &quot;water the plants&quot;,
       done: false
      },
      {
       desc: &quot;call my mom&quot;,
       done: true
      }
    ]
    })

**note:** the &quot;task&quot; object used here is just an example, modify the query accordingly to your use case.  


  [1]: https://firebase.google.com/docs/firestore/manage-data/add-data

